The limen of the loved one's door was the natural confidant of all a Roman lover’s woes and disappointments, and the recipient of his most earnest protestations. In 1.16 awbole poem is devoted to retailing the varied experiences of a limen, which betrays the consessions of a rejected but still hopesul lover. Strange that the one merit of such a confidant—that it could keep a secret—should be so wantonly sacrificed. Cp. Catull. 67.
